<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-05-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-05-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="77" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d77">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Lot 54D423</note>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Extracts]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Memorandum Prepared in the Department of
                                    State</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-05-03">May 3,
                                    1951</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p rend="center">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Agenda</hi><note n="1" xml:id="d77fn1">The
                                    remainder of this memorandum is printed on <ref target="#pg_1038">p. 1038</ref>.</note>
                            </p>
                            <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                            <p rend="center">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">ii. australia and new zealand</hi>
                            </p>
                            <p rend="flushleft">
                                <hi rend="italic">Security Arrangement</hi>
                            </p>
                            <list>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">a</hi>.</label>
                                <item>Get further views of the Pentagon as to the nature of
                                    “consultation” (see President’s statement)<note n="2" xml:id="d77fn2">For text of the President’s statement of
                                        April 18, see the Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, April 30, 1951, p. 699.</note> and the
                                    views of the Joint Chiefs with reference to Articles VII and
                                    VIII of the Canberra draft.</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">b</hi>.</label>
                                <item>Prepare for and fix date for concluding negotiations with
                                    Australia and New Zealand, presumably in Washington after
                                    Spender arrives.</item>
                                <label>
                                    <hi rend="italic">c</hi>.</label>
                                <item>Clear with Foreign Relations Committee.</item>
                            </list>
                            <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>